// The synthetic ensures has shape
//     `(r1@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr)) && (r2@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr))
//        ==> det_extract_range_impl_equal(r1, r2)`,
// so the two view-equalities live INSIDE the antecedent — they are not
// free hypotheses.  The previous attempt asserted them unconditionally and
// (correctly) failed.  Branch on the full LHS; inside the then-branch both
// conjuncts become path conditions, so transitivity through the shared
// right-hand side `extract_range(h@, *kr)` lets z3 line up the two
// `extract_range(h@, *kr)` terms and close map extensional equality.
if (r1@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr)) && (r2@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr)) {
    // Map extensionality (`=~=`): both views are extensionally equal to
    // the same Map, hence to each other.  Re-stating the two antecedent
    // conjuncts as asserts here gives z3 a concrete instance of the
    // shared term `extract_range(h@, *kr)` to anchor the trigger.
    assert(r1@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr));
    assert(r2@ =~= extract_range(h@, *kr));
    assert(r1@ =~= r2@);
    assert(r1@ == r2@);
}
